<subSubSection id="CD8744AE7564843AFF41FF2FFDB5FA56" pageId="1" pageNumber="585" type="description">
<paragraph id="852217257564843AFF41FF2FFF42FF69" blockId="1.[151,576,153,215]" box="[151,235,189,215]" pageId="1" pageNumber="585">
(
<figureCitation id="1DA60BA07564843AFF76FF2FFF49FF69" box="[160,224,189,215]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1919,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sinocyrtaspis megalobia sp. nov.: A–B, D–E. pronotum: A, D. dorsal view; B, E. lateral view; C, F, G–I, K. apex of abdomen: C, F. lateral view; G, I. dorsal view; H. apical view; J, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; K. latero-ventral view; M. genitalia in apical view. A–C, G–H, K–M. male; D–F, I–J. female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3602618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3602618/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="585">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="852217257564843AFF41FE97FC36FED6" blockId="1.[151,1437,261,1908]" pageId="1" pageNumber="585">
<emphasis id="B7E9CB377564843AFF41FE97FEDFFE9E" bold="true" box="[151,374,261,288]" pageId="1" pageNumber="585">Description. Male.</emphasis>
Body small, robust. Fastigium verticis conical, narrower than antennal scape, apex obtusely rounded, with a thin median sulcus. Eyes oval, obviously protruding forward. Apical segment of maxillary palpus slightly longer than subapical one, slightly swollen apically, truncate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="852217257564843AFF11FEE0FF61FE49" blockId="1.[151,1437,261,1908]" pageId="1" pageNumber="585">
Pronotum somewhat long, reaching posterior margin of seventh abdominal tergite; anterior margin somewhat straight while posterior margin obtusely rounded; metazona gently extended outward and rather strikingly raised (
<figureCitation id="1DA60BA07564843AFF76FE2BFF74FE6D" box="[160,221,441,467]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1919,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sinocyrtaspis megalobia sp. nov.: A–B, D–E. pronotum: A, D. dorsal view; B, E. lateral view; C, F, G–I, K. apex of abdomen: C, F. lateral view; G, I. dorsal view; H. apical view; J, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; K. latero-ventral view; M. genitalia in apical view. A–C, G–H, K–M. male; D–F, I–J. female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3602618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3602618/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="585">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
A–B); lateral lobe longer than deep, posterior margin slightly expanded ventrally, without humeral sinus (
<figureCitation id="1DA60BA07564843AFAB9FE2BFF10FE49" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1919,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sinocyrtaspis megalobia sp. nov.: A–B, D–E. pronotum: A, D. dorsal view; B, E. lateral view; C, F, G–I, K. apex of abdomen: C, F. lateral view; G, I. dorsal view; H. apical view; J, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; K. latero-ventral view; M. genitalia in apical view. A–C, G–H, K–M. male; D–F, I–J. female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3602618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3602618/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="585">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="852217257564843AFF11FD93FB76FDA5" blockId="1.[151,1437,261,1908]" box="[199,1247,513,540]" pageId="1" pageNumber="585">Tegmina short, completely covered by pronotum, invisible in lateral view; hind wings absent.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="852217257564843AFF11FDB7FF73FD6E" blockId="1.[151,1437,261,1908]" pageId="1" pageNumber="585">All femora unarmed ventrally, genicular lobes with apices obtuse. Fore coxae with 1 short spine; tibiae with 5 spines respectively on both sides of ventral surface, tibial tympana open on both sides, ovoid. Middle tibiae with 4 inner and 6 outer spines on ventral surface. Hind tibiae with 1 outer spine on ventral surface as well as 21–23 spines respectively on both sides of dorsal surface, bearing 2 pairs of ventral apical spurs and 1 pair of dorsal apical spurs.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="852217257564843AFF11FD4BFEE9FBAD" blockId="1.[151,1437,261,1908]" pageId="1" pageNumber="585">
Lateral margins of ninth abdominal tergite strongly prolonged posteriorly (
<figureCitation id="1DA60BA07564843AFC2AFD4BFBF8FD4D" box="[1020,1105,729,755]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1919,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sinocyrtaspis megalobia sp. nov.: A–B, D–E. pronotum: A, D. dorsal view; B, E. lateral view; C, F, G–I, K. apex of abdomen: C, F. lateral view; G, I. dorsal view; H. apical view; J, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; K. latero-ventral view; M. genitalia in apical view. A–C, G–H, K–M. male; D–F, I–J. female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3602618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3602618/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="585">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
); posterior margin arc-shaped concave. Tenth abdominal tergite expanded posteriorly, 1/3 basal area wide, 2/3 apical area narrow (
<figureCitation id="1DA60BA07564843AFB3AFD6FFAEAFCA9" box="[1260,1347,765,791]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1919,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sinocyrtaspis megalobia sp. nov.: A–B, D–E. pronotum: A, D. dorsal view; B, E. lateral view; C, F, G–I, K. apex of abdomen: C, F. lateral view; G, I. dorsal view; H. apical view; J, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; K. latero-ventral view; M. genitalia in apical view. A–C, G–H, K–M. male; D–F, I–J. female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3602618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3602618/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="585">Fig. 1G</figureCitation>
), with a narrow longitudinal split in the midline, terminal of lateral lobe obtusely rounded (
<figureCitation id="1DA60BA07564843AFBFAFCB3FB2CFC85" box="[1068,1157,801,827]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1919,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sinocyrtaspis megalobia sp. nov.: A–B, D–E. pronotum: A, D. dorsal view; B, E. lateral view; C, F, G–I, K. apex of abdomen: C, F. lateral view; G, I. dorsal view; H. apical view; J, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; K. latero-ventral view; M. genitalia in apical view. A–C, G–H, K–M. male; D–F, I–J. female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3602618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3602618/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="585">Fig. 1K</figureCitation>
). Cerci slightly elongate, faintly bent inward, dorsal margin of 2/3 basal area conspicuously expanded internally and dorsally, phylloid (
<figureCitation id="1DA60BA07564843AFAB9FCD7FF75FC3A" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1919,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sinocyrtaspis megalobia sp. nov.: A–B, D–E. pronotum: A, D. dorsal view; B, E. lateral view; C, F, G–I, K. apex of abdomen: C, F. lateral view; G, I. dorsal view; H. apical view; J, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; K. latero-ventral view; M. genitalia in apical view. A–C, G–H, K–M. male; D–F, I–J. female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3602618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3602618/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="585">Fig. 1C, H</figureCitation>
); 1/3 apical area of cerci spiniform, faintly compressed, terminal obtusely rounded (
<figureCitation id="1DA60BA07564843AFBAFFCFBFB79FC3D" box="[1145,1232,873,899]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1919,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sinocyrtaspis megalobia sp. nov.: A–B, D–E. pronotum: A, D. dorsal view; B, E. lateral view; C, F, G–I, K. apex of abdomen: C, F. lateral view; G, I. dorsal view; H. apical view; J, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; K. latero-ventral view; M. genitalia in apical view. A–C, G–H, K–M. male; D–F, I–J. female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3602618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3602618/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="585">Fig. 1H</figureCitation>
). Genitalia sclerotized, exposed, longer than subgenital plate, terminal expanded, distal, edge rolled backward (
<figureCitation id="1DA60BA07564843AFB64FC1FFAB9FC19" box="[1202,1296,909,935]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1919,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sinocyrtaspis megalobia sp. nov.: A–B, D–E. pronotum: A, D. dorsal view; B, E. lateral view; C, F, G–I, K. apex of abdomen: C, F. lateral view; G, I. dorsal view; H. apical view; J, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; K. latero-ventral view; M. genitalia in apical view. A–C, G–H, K–M. male; D–F, I–J. female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3602618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3602618/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="585">Fig. 1M</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate nearly rectangular, basal area with an angular notch, lateral margins of 2/3 apical area faintly extended dorsad (
<figureCitation id="1DA60BA07564843AFF76FC47FF51FC51" box="[160,248,981,1007]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1919,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sinocyrtaspis megalobia sp. nov.: A–B, D–E. pronotum: A, D. dorsal view; B, E. lateral view; C, F, G–I, K. apex of abdomen: C, F. lateral view; G, I. dorsal view; H. apical view; J, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; K. latero-ventral view; M. genitalia in apical view. A–C, G–H, K–M. male; D–F, I–J. female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3602618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3602618/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="585">Fig. 1K</figureCitation>
), posterior margin with a triangular concavity; styli stout, inserted on apico-lateral margins of subgenital plate (
<figureCitation id="1DA60BA07564843AFF0BFC6BFE9BFBAD" box="[221,306,1017,1043]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1919,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sinocyrtaspis megalobia sp. nov.: A–B, D–E. pronotum: A, D. dorsal view; B, E. lateral view; C, F, G–I, K. apex of abdomen: C, F. lateral view; G, I. dorsal view; H. apical view; J, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; K. latero-ventral view; M. genitalia in apical view. A–C, G–H, K–M. male; D–F, I–J. female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3602618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3602618/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="585">Fig. 1L</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="852217257564843AFF11FB8CFDF0FB55" blockId="1.[151,1437,261,1908]" pageId="1" pageNumber="585">
<emphasis id="B7E9CB377564843AFF11FB8CFE8CFB86" bold="true" box="[199,293,1054,1080]" pageId="1" pageNumber="585">Female.</emphasis>
Pronotum slightly short, slightly surpassing anterior margin of second abdominal tergite. Lateral margins of ninth abdominal tergite rather protruding unusually backward (
<figureCitation id="1DA60BA07564843AFC78FBD3FBABFBE5" box="[942,1026,1089,1115]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1919,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sinocyrtaspis megalobia sp. nov.: A–B, D–E. pronotum: A, D. dorsal view; B, E. lateral view; C, F, G–I, K. apex of abdomen: C, F. lateral view; G, I. dorsal view; H. apical view; J, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; K. latero-ventral view; M. genitalia in apical view. A–C, G–H, K–M. male; D–F, I–J. female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3602618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3602618/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="585">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
), reaching middle area of subgenital plate; posterior margin arc-shaped concave (
<figureCitation id="1DA60BA07564843AFD5DFBF7FD71FBC1" box="[651,728,1125,1151]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1919,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sinocyrtaspis megalobia sp. nov.: A–B, D–E. pronotum: A, D. dorsal view; B, E. lateral view; C, F, G–I, K. apex of abdomen: C, F. lateral view; G, I. dorsal view; H. apical view; J, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; K. latero-ventral view; M. genitalia in apical view. A–C, G–H, K–M. male; D–F, I–J. female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3602618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3602618/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="585">
Fig. 
<date id="F12331E57564843AFD16FBF7FD71FBC1" box="[704,728,1125,1151]" pageId="1" pageNumber="585">1I</date>
</figureCitation>
). Tenth abdominal tergite slightly elongated posteriorly, posterior margin sunken in the middle (
<figureCitation id="1DA60BA07564843AFDCFFB1BFDCFFB1D" box="[537,614,1161,1187]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1919,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sinocyrtaspis megalobia sp. nov.: A–B, D–E. pronotum: A, D. dorsal view; B, E. lateral view; C, F, G–I, K. apex of abdomen: C, F. lateral view; G, I. dorsal view; H. apical view; J, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; K. latero-ventral view; M. genitalia in apical view. A–C, G–H, K–M. male; D–F, I–J. female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3602618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3602618/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="585">
Fig. 
<date id="F12331E57564843AFD98FB1BFDCFFB1D" box="[590,614,1161,1187]" pageId="1" pageNumber="585">1I</date>
</figureCitation>
). Cerci conical, apices somewhat blunt. Ovipositor robust at base, apical half moderately bent dorsad, apex acute; dorsal and ventral margins smooth, (
<figureCitation id="1DA60BA07564843AFBCDFB3FFBDBFB79" box="[1051,1138,1197,1223]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1919,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sinocyrtaspis megalobia sp. nov.: A–B, D–E. pronotum: A, D. dorsal view; B, E. lateral view; C, F, G–I, K. apex of abdomen: C, F. lateral view; G, I. dorsal view; H. apical view; J, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; K. latero-ventral view; M. genitalia in apical view. A–C, G–H, K–M. male; D–F, I–J. female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3602618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3602618/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="585">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate peltate, posterior margin a bit concave (
<figureCitation id="1DA60BA07564843AFE2DFB43FDE0FB55" box="[507,585,1233,1259]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1919,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sinocyrtaspis megalobia sp. nov.: A–B, D–E. pronotum: A, D. dorsal view; B, E. lateral view; C, F, G–I, K. apex of abdomen: C, F. lateral view; G, I. dorsal view; H. apical view; J, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; K. latero-ventral view; M. genitalia in apical view. A–C, G–H, K–M. male; D–F, I–J. female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3602618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3602618/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="585">Fig. 1J</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="852217257564843AFF11FB67FB28FA21" blockId="1.[151,1437,261,1908]" pageId="1" pageNumber="585">
<emphasis id="B7E9CB377564843AFF11FB67FEE6FAAE" bold="true" box="[199,335,1269,1296]" pageId="1" pageNumber="585">Coloration.</emphasis>
Body green when alive, while yellowish green when dried and pinned. Eyes brown. Fastigium verticis light brown. Disc of pronotum with 1 broad longitudinal light brown stripe, lateral margins black brown; outer edges of stripe with 1 longitudinal yellow stripe respectively, of which posterior areas inconspicuous (
<figureCitation id="1DA60BA07564843AFAC5FAAFFA39FAE6" box="[1299,1424,1341,1368]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1919,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sinocyrtaspis megalobia sp. nov.: A–B, D–E. pronotum: A, D. dorsal view; B, E. lateral view; C, F, G–I, K. apex of abdomen: C, F. lateral view; G, I. dorsal view; H. apical view; J, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; K. latero-ventral view; M. genitalia in apical view. A–C, G–H, K–M. male; D–F, I–J. female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3602618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3602618/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="585">Fig. 1A, D</figureCitation>
). Dorsal surface of abdomen with 1 longitudinal light brown stripe. Apical of male genitalia black (
<figureCitation id="1DA60BA07564843AFB0BFAF3FA92FAC5" box="[1245,1339,1377,1403]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1919,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sinocyrtaspis megalobia sp. nov.: A–B, D–E. pronotum: A, D. dorsal view; B, E. lateral view; C, F, G–I, K. apex of abdomen: C, F. lateral view; G, I. dorsal view; H. apical view; J, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; K. latero-ventral view; M. genitalia in apical view. A–C, G–H, K–M. male; D–F, I–J. female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3602618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3602618/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="585">Fig. 1M</figureCitation>
). Apices of all third tarsi and claws brown, apical area of dorsal spines on hind tibiae black brown.
</paragraph>
